create.description: Creates a new object with the specified prototype object and properties.
create.name: create

defineProperty.description: Adds the named property described by a given descriptor to an object.
defineProperty.name: defineProperty

defineProperties.description: Adds the named properties described by the given descriptors to an object.
defineProperties.name: defineProperties

getOwnPropertyDescriptor.description: Returns a property descriptor for a named property on an object.
getOwnPropertyDescriptor.name: getOwnPropertyDescriptor

keys.description: Returns an array containing the names of all of the given object's own enumerable properties.
keys.name: keys

getOwnPropertyNames.description: Returns an array containing the names of all of the given object's own enumerable and non-enumerable properties.
getOwnPropertyNames.name: getOwnPropertyNames

getPrototypeOf.description: Returns the prototype of the specified object.
getPrototypeOf.name: getPrototypeOf

preventExtensions.description: Prevents any extensions of an object.
preventExtensions.name: preventExtensions

isExtensible.description: Determine if extending of an object is allowed.
isExtensible.name: isExtensible

seal.description: Prevents other code from deleting properties of an object.
seal.name: seal

isSealed.description: Determine if an object is sealed.
isSealed.name: isSealed

freeze.description: Freezes an object: other code can't delete or change any properties.
freeze.name: freeze

isFrozen.description: Determine if an object was frozen.
isFrozen.name: isFrozen

constructor.description: Specifies the function that creates an object's prototype.
constructor.name: constructor

hasOwnProperty.description: Returns a boolean indicating whether an object contains the specified property as a direct property of that object and not inherited through the prototype chain.
hasOwnProperty.name: hasOwnProperty

propertyIsEnumerable.description: Returns a boolean indicating if the internal ECMAScript DontEnum attribute is set.
propertyIsEnumerable.name: propertyIsEnumerable

toString.description: Returns a string representation of the object.
toString.name: toString

valueOf.description: Returns the primitive value of the specified object.
valueOf.name: valueOf
